--- SCOPE ---
File: veomni/distributed/torch_parallelize.py
Function: _build_fsdp2_model (line ~398 in veomni 0.1.4)

WHY THIS IS SAFE:
  Every rank calls _load_state_dict(weights_path) and reads the FULL checkpoint
  (VeOmni's own log: "Every rank would read weights from disk").
  distribute_tensor(t, mesh, [Shard(0)], src_data_rank=0) then fires
  dist.scatter() to send rank0's copy to all other ranks — but every rank
  already has an identical copy.

  src_data_rank=None → Shard._shard_tensor() skips mesh_scatter() and calls
  _split_tensor()[my_rank] instead — a pure local indexing op, zero comms.

